---
description: Coding conventions, naming, and safe-change guidance
---

# Conventions

- API files: app/server/api/<path>.<method>.ts where method ∈ {get, post, patch, delete}
- Service-first: API handlers should validate/authorize, then delegate to app/server/services/*
- Validation: Use Zod schemas from app/schema/zod.ts where available
- Auth: Use app/server/middleware/auth.ts globally, requireAdmin.ts for admin/* scopes
- Error handling: Prefer withErrorHandler.ts or handleApiError.ts; Plaid errors via plaidApiError.ts
- Data access: Use app/server/clients/prismaClient.ts; keep Prisma access inside service/repository layers when practical
- Logging: app/server/logger.ts (Winston + GCP logging compatible). Forecast engine has its own logger.
- Rate limit: app/server/lib/rateLimitRedis.ts for per-route limiting where needed
- Time and decimals:
  - Amounts are Decimal(19,2) at DB. Use domain helpers (e.g., bankers-rounding.ts, calculateAdjustedBalance.ts) and avoid JS float math
  - Time-related logic centralizes in forecast/DateTimeService.ts and related utilities; tests run in TZ=UTC

# Naming

- Branches/commits: follow CONTRIBUTING.md; DCO sign-off required
- Models/tables: singular Prisma models (Account, RegisterEntry, Reoccurrence, etc.)
- Encrypted fields: annotated with comments like /// @encrypted (and @encryption:hash(...)) in schema.prisma
- Migrations: timestamped directories under prisma/migrations with a clear name; microservice has its own prisma/migrations as needed

# Adding or changing API endpoints safely

1) Place new handler under app/server/api with <path>.<method>.ts
2) Early authorize (session user, account membership, admin as required)
3) Validate payload (Zod). Normalize/parse dates with parseOptionalIsoQuery.ts if applicable
4) Delegate to a service; do not embed complex logic in the route
5) Return minimal DTOs; avoid leaking internal fields (e.g., hashed/encrypted columns)
6) Add unit tests under app/server/api/__tests__/ covering success + error cases
7) If used by UI, create composables/stores and write E2E coverage where appropriate

# Schema and data model changes

- Edit app/prisma/schema.prisma
- Generate migration (Prisma). Ensure app/microservice schemas stay in sync if the microservice relies on the same models
- Run pnpm --filter dineros-app exec prisma generate after changes
- Encryption:
  - Mark sensitive fields with /// @encrypted (and hashes with @encryption:hash(...))
  - Generated migrators appear under prisma/reencrypt; ensure post-restore/key-rotation flows integrate them
- Add/adjust seeds in app/prisma/seed.ts only for generally applicable reference data (e.g., intervals, countries)

# Forecast engine changes

- Compose via ForecastEngine orchestrator with services in server/services/forecast/*
- Extend types in forecast/types.ts and keep DateTimeService in sync for boundary logic
- Add or update tests in server/services/forecast/__tests__ (unit + integration + regression snapshots)
- Use ModernCacheService for performance-sensitive paths to keep tests fast and memory stable

# Background jobs and cron

- New recurring tasks: add under server/cron/*.ts (nuxt-cron)
- Long-running or batch operations: consider enqueueing via server/queues/* with BullMQ
- Provide admin/test stubs (tasks/* routes) carefully gated; see existing tasks endpoints for patterns

# Security & secrets

- Never commit real secrets. Use .env.example placeholders.
- Respect server/envSchema.ts requirements when adding new env vars (Zod-validated)
- For Plaid and other integrations, normalize errors and avoid logging sensitive payloads
- Field-level encryption keys are provided via env; see deployment templates and encryption docs

# Testing expectations

- Unit/integration: Vitest with TZ=UTC; see app/package.json scripts
- E2E: Playwright specs under app/tests/e2e; visual snapshots split for authed/public
- For new endpoints/services, add Vitest coverage first; add E2E if UI interactions are changed

# CI/CD touch points

- PR workflow (pr.yml) runs lint/test/security and builds + deploys to staging in this repo (fork PRs skip deploy)
- Default-branch workflow (main.yml) builds and deploys to production
- CodeQL weekly, optional Sonar scan (manual)
